    "<h1>âš¡ EV Hub â€“ Project Documentation</h1>\n",
    "<p>\n",
    "EV Hub is a full-stack electric vehicle web application built using:\n",
    "</p>\n",
    "<ul>\n",
    "    <li><strong>Flask</strong> â€“ REST API backend</li>\n",
    "    <li><strong>Django</strong> â€“ Frontend & routing</li>\n",
    "    <li><strong>HTML + Bootstrap</strong> â€“ UI</li>\n",
    "</ul>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div class=\"box\">\n",
    "<h2>1. Project Architecture</h2>\n",
    "<p>\n",
    "The system uses a <strong>decoupled architecture</strong>:\n",
    "</p>\n",
    "<ul>\n",
    "    <li>Flask exposes EV data and calculations as JSON</li>\n",
    "    <li>Django consumes the API and renders HTML pages</li>\n",
    "</ul>\n",
    "\n",
    "<pre>\n",
    "Browser\n",
    "   â†“\n",
    "Django (Templates, Views)\n",
    "   â†“  HTTP (JSON)\n",
    "Flask API\n",
    "</pre>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div class=\"box\">\n",
    "<h2>2. Folder Structure</h2>\n",
    "\n",
    "<pre>\n",
    "ev_Hub/\n",
    "â”œâ”€â”€ flask_api/\n",
    "â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ app.py\n",
    "â”‚   â””â”€â”€ cars_data.py\n",
    "â”‚\n",
    "â””â”€â”€ ev_web/\n",
    "    â”œâ”€â”€ config/\n",
    "    â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ settings.py\n",
    "    â”‚   â””â”€â”€ urls.py\n",
    "    â”‚\n",
    "    â”œâ”€â”€ cars/\n",
    "    â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ views.py\n",
    "    â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ urls.py\n",
    "    â”‚   â””â”€â”€ templates/\n",
    "    â”‚       â””â”€â”€ cars/\n",
    "    â”‚           â”œâ”€â”€ car_list.html\n",
    "    â”‚           â”œâ”€â”€ car_details.html\n",
    "    â”‚           â””â”€â”€ compare.html\n",
    "</pre>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div class=\"box\">\n",
    "<h2>3. Flask API Responsibilities</h2>\n",
    "\n",
    "<ul>\n",
    "    <li>Provide EV car data</li>\n",
    "    <li>Calculate trip feasibility</li>\n",
    "    <li>Return JSON responses</li>\n",
    "</ul>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h3>Example Endpoint</h3>\n",
    "<pre>\n",
    "GET /api/cars\n",
    "GET /api/cars/&lt;id&gt;\n",
    "GET /api/range-check?car_id=1&amp;trip_km=120\n",
    "</pre>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div class=\"box\">\n",
    "<h2>4. Django Responsibilities</h2>\n",
    "\n",
    "<ul>\n",
    "    <li>Render UI pages</li>\n",
    "    <li>Handle user input (forms)</li>\n",
    "    <li>Call Flask API using <code>requests</code></li>\n",
    "</ul>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h3>Example Django View</h3>\n",
    "<pre>\n",
    "def car_list(request):\n",
    "    r = requests.get(\"http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/cars\")\n",
    "    cars = r.json()\n",
    "    return render(request, \"cars/car_list.html\", {\"cars\": cars})\n",
    "</pre>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div class=\"box\">\n",
    "<h2>5. Car List Page</h2>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>\n",
    "Displays:\n",
    "</p>\n",
    "<ul>\n",
    "    <li>EV brand and model</li>\n",
    "    <li>Battery percentage</li>\n",
    "    <li>Estimated range</li>\n",
    "</ul>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h3>Battery Bar Logic</h3>\n",
    "<pre>\n",
    "&lt;div class=\"progress\"&gt;\n",
    "    &lt;div class=\"progress-bar\"\n",
    "         style=\"width: {{ car.battery_pct }}%;\"&gt;\n",
    "    &lt;/div&gt;\n",
    "&lt;/div&gt;\n",
    "</pre>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div class=\"box\">\n",
    "<h2>6. Range Check Feature</h2>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>\n",
    "Users enter trip distance in kilometers.  \n",
    "The system checks if the selected EV can complete the trip.\n",
    "</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h3>Logic</h3>\n",
    "<ul>\n",
    "    <li>User enters distance</li>\n",
    "    <li>Django sends request to Flask</li>\n",
    "    <li>Flask compares range vs trip</li>\n",
    "</ul>\n",
    "\n",
    "<pre>\n",
    "if trip_km <= car_range:\n",
    "    return \"Trip possible\"\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    return \"Charging required\"\n",
    "</pre>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div class=\"box\">\n",
    "<h2>7. Car Comparison Feature</h2>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>\n",
    "Users can compare two EVs based on:\n",
